{{Portal|Anglicanism}}'''Joseph Amritanand''' was [[Anglican Bishop of Calcutta|Bishop of Calcutta]] in the mid 20th century. He had served as the [[Anglican Bishop of Lucknow|Bishop of Lucknow]] in 1962, then under the ''Church of India, Pakistan, Burma and Ceylon'' (1948-1970). He was the first [[Anglican Bishop of Calcutta|Bishop of Calcutta]] after the establishment of the [[Church of North India]].<ref name=CNICalcutta>[http://cnicalcutta.org/bishop_joseph_amritanand.html Joseph Amritanand Bishop of Calcutta, CNI 1970 – 1982]</ref><ref>[[Crockford's Clerical Directory]]1947-48 Oxford, [[OUP]], 1947</ref>

