The following is a list of current [[Catholic Church|Catholic]] religious institutes. Most are [[Catholic Church|Roman Catholic]], however [[Eastern Catholic Churches|Eastern Catholic]] institutes are included.
The list given here includes not only examples of pontifical-right institutes but also some that are only of [[Diocese|diocesan]] right. It includes even some [[association of the faithful|associations]] formed with a view to ''becoming'' religious institutes but not yet canonically erected even on the diocesan level.
The list does not distinguish between institutes that historically would be classified either as "[[Catholic religious order|orders]]" or as "[[Congregation (Catholic)#Type of religious institute|congregations]]".
Institutes are listed alphabetically by their ''common'' names, not their ''official'' ones. For example, the [[Society of Jesus|Jesuits]], officially called the Society of Jesus, would be listed under 'J' rather than under 'S.' If an institute's official name is used more often than a nickname, it will be listed as such.
